<Project Sdk="Microsoft.NET.Sdk">

  <PropertyGroup>
    <PackageVersion>1.11.0</PackageVersion>
    <FileVersion>1.11.0.0</FileVersion>
    <Version>1.11.0</Version>
    <Authors>skuirrels</Authors>
    <Description>DuckDB and DuckLake provider for Entity Framework Core.</Description>
    <PackageTags>DuckDB; DuckLake; Entity Framework Core; EF Core</PackageTags>
    <PackageIcon>DuckDB_icon-lightmode.png</PackageIcon>
    <PackageLicenseExpression>MIT</PackageLicenseExpression>
    <PackageReadmeFile>README.md</PackageReadmeFile>
    <RepositoryUrl>https://github.com/skuirrels/DuckDB.EFCoreProvider</RepositoryUrl>
    <RepositoryType>git</RepositoryType>
    <!-- Ship the XML documentation file so the public API docs reach consumers' IntelliSense.
         CS1591 (missing XML comment) is suppressed: EF Core providers necessarily expose many
         "pubternal" members that carry the standard internal-API boilerplate instead. -->
    <GenerateDocumentationFile>true</GenerateDocumentationFile>
    <NoWarn>$(NoWarn);EF1001;EF9100;CS1591</NoWarn>
    <IsPackable>true</IsPackable>
    <!-- Compare the packed public API against the last published release (see Directory.Build.props). -->
    <PackageValidationBaselineVersion>1.10.2</PackageValidationBaselineVersion>
    <PackageReleaseNotes>
1.11.0
- Add provider-neutral immutable cold-tier retention through fingerprinted planning and verified, atomic generation publication, preserving the previous generation for rollback and separately authorised cleanup.
- Add bounded first archive publication over an aligned [from, cutoff) lifecycle range, with exact idempotent retry semantics.
- Add generic local, shared-descendant, month/day, failure-injection, exact-catalogue, MinIO, and catalogue-scale acceptance coverage. The provider does not interpret business retention or automatically delete obsolete remote generations.

1.10.2
- Replace application-specific tiered-storage entities, identifiers, lifecycle fields, release evidence, and the partition diagram with provider-neutral record examples across the README, guide, sample, validation text, and tests. No public API changes.

1.10.1
- Fix tiered partition pruning for ordered/limited query shapes: derived owner/lifecycle predicates are now collected against a stable select shape and applied in one immutable update, preserving server-side ORDER BY, OFFSET/LIMIT, keyset predicates, parameterisation, and root/descendant binding resolution.
- Add a generic tiered-view query-composition and lifecycle matrix for ToTieredView(...) and WithReadModel&lt;TReadModel&gt;(), with SQL and EXPLAIN file-pruning evidence, nullable DateOnly/partition coverage, context/model-cache concurrency checks, real-cloud opt-in failure matrices, and a published compatibility report. The 1.10.1-rc.1 package passed the complete compatibility matrix with no additional provider defects.

1.10.0
- Add WithTieredView(...) on roots and descendants so the provider can create and maintain hot/cold union views without registering duplicate CLR read models; add ToTieredView(...) so separate read-only contexts receive equivalent provider-derived partition predicates with a physical contract marker that rejects independently deployed partition-plan drift; support explicit names, shared descendants, every existing archive maintenance path, local file-pruning evidence, and disposable object-storage coverage.

1.9.0
- Add explicit physical Hive partition names to tiered-storage exact/year/month/day declarations, including inherited child layouts, typed hot/cold views, persisted layout checks, archive maintenance, and metadata-driven query pruning.

1.8.0
- Support deterministic root-scoped bindings and combined hot+cold views when one child table participates in multiple independent tiered roots; reject ambiguous row ownership before external writes or hot deletion.

1.7.0
- Add generic scoped reconciliation, explicit root/child tombstones, cold-to-hot aggregate restoration, bounded conflict diagnostics, and immutable full-generation compaction.
- Add archive-contract inspection, fingerprinted rewrite plans, caller-supplied column mappings, verified immutable contract rewrites, and composite child foreign-key traversal.
- Add strongly typed Parquet writer controls, summary/representative manifests, persisted generation/file inventory, read-only cleanup planning, remote catalogue-backed active file discovery, and storage capability preflight.
- Add install-and-load, load-only, and caller-managed extension provisioning modes plus DateOnly lifecycle selectors.

1.6.0
- Support nullable tier lifecycle properties and nullable lifecycle partition transforms; NULL aggregates remain hot until completed and eligible.
- Add configurable MatchBy(...) keys on roots and children, including composite keys and explicit externally-enforced uniqueness, with persisted archive-contract compatibility checks.
- Detect corrections and reopened roots before normal archival. ReconcileArchiveTierAsync publishes approved late/corrected data through a verified immutable Parquet generation and an atomic control/view switch.
- Return detailed TierArchiveResult evidence with per-table counts, archive windows, watermark transitions, revision, paths/files, no-op state, and safe partial failure results.
- Add injected failure/retry coverage and a reusable MinIO/disposable real-AWS S3 matrix for archive, restart, publication, partial cleanup, reconciliation, and additive schema evolution.

1.5.0
- Add a first-class DuckLake backend profile in the main package through UseDuckLake(...): local metadata or named secrets, safe attachment before EF uses provider-owned or caller-owned connections, read-only mode, catalog creation controls, automatic metadata migration, and connection-scoped data-path override.
- Support DuckLake LINQ, transactions, EnsureCreated, tracked CRUD with affected-row concurrency checks, appender BulkInsert, and MERGE-based Upsert.
- Fail clearly for unsupported DuckLake sequences/store-generated values, SaveChanges batching, tiered storage, EF migrations, and EnsureDeleted; omit unsupported physical constraints/indexes from initial DDL. Add an official catalog-migration fixture, isolated PostgreSQL/MinIO named-secret coverage on Linux CI, production documentation, and a runnable sample.

1.4.0
- Add ordered root-owned PartitionBy plans with exact/year/month/day transforms, inherited child layouts, metadata-driven query pruning, and versioned compatibility checks.
- Add a runnable Google Cloud Storage tiered-storage mode using DuckDB's TYPE gcs secret and gcs:// paths, with MinIO interoperability coverage and production guidance for GCS HMAC credentials and lifecycle retention. No public API changes.

1.3.0
- Fix nullable ExecuteSqlInterpolated parameters and normalize raw-SQL parameter names centrally.
- Emit and enforce foreign keys during table creation; normalize unsupported cascade actions to NO ACTION and add opt-in table rebuilds for constraint changes.
- Add typed ExportToParquet and ExportToParquetAsync APIs with parameter preservation, typed partitions, overwrite policy, compression, and cancellation.
- Add provider-owned extension loading and connection initialization for httpfs, Azure, secrets, and other DuckDB extensions.
- Translate SplitPart, sample standard deviation, ArgMax, and ArgMin through EF.Functions.
- Harden tiered aggregate cleanup for enforced foreign keys and reject unsafe caller transactions before multi-table archival.

1.2.4
- Performance: blob reads allocate roughly half as much. Materializing a byte[] column no longer double-buffers the driver's stream through a growing MemoryStream plus ToArray(); DuckDB.NET's blob stream is seekable with a known length, so the provider reads once into an exact-size array. On 2,000 rows x 4 KB blobs, allocations fell from 16.49 MB to 8.51 MB and Gen0 collections halved. No public API changes.

1.2.3
- Performance: further reduce managed allocations in provider-owned hot paths. SaveChanges insert/update/delete batching now decides statement merging without allocating per-command LINQ iterators (~12% fewer bytes on a 4,000-row batched insert: 19.74 MB -&gt; 17.42 MB). Query SQL generation drops a per-table allocation in the file-source lookup, and remote-archive path detection uses a source-generated regex. No public API changes.

1.2.2
- Performance: reduce managed allocations in provider-owned write hot paths and array parameter binding. Bulk insert now uses typed appender delegates for common CLR property types, SaveChanges batching reuses column-modification views more aggressively, and upsert now stages each batch through DuckDB's appender into a temporary table before a set-based INSERT ... ON CONFLICT merge. In the local 1,000-row allocation benchmark, UpsertBatch improved from 45.706 ms / 2203.38 KB to 24.455 ms / 1046.66 KB. No public API changes.

1.2.1
- Harden tiered storage archive handling. Cold views now require a real archive watermark and at least one archive file, so empty or missing cold archives no longer hide hot rows. Archive cleanup is key-aware, preserving late/backdated hot rows unless the same primary key is present in cold storage. Tiered SQL now consistently honours schema-qualified table mappings, and malformed partition directories are skipped during local purge. No public API changes.

1.2.0
- Tiered storage: the cold archive can now live on an object store. Point archivePath at an s3:// (also gcs://, r2://, azure://) URL and DuckDB reads and writes the Parquet there directly via httpfs; hot data stays in the local .duckdb file. Load httpfs and configure credentials with an EF Core connection interceptor (the provider now opens its own connections through EF, so the interceptor runs for archive operations too). Partitioned writes, incremental appends, idempotent re-runs, and the crash-safety invariant behave identically on S3 (verified against MinIO). Retention on object storage: PurgeArchiveOlderThan throws NotSupportedException for a remote archive — use a bucket lifecycle rule on the hive-partitioned prefix instead. See docs/TIERED-STORAGE.md.

1.1.0
- Add tiered storage: keep recent ("hot") rows in the writable DuckDB file and offload older ("cold") rows to hive-partitioned Parquet, then report across the whole history with LINQ. Tiering works over a relational aggregate (root + declared children), governed by the root's date. The hot side stays ordinary EF Core (regular entities, relationships, SaveChanges, Include); cold reporting uses a keyless read-model per table mapped to a generated union view. Configure with modelBuilder.ToTieredStore&lt;TRoot&gt;(r =&gt; r.Date, archivePath, granularity).WithReadModel&lt;TReport&gt;().Including&lt;TChild&gt;(...). Create views with EnsureCreated() (automatic) or EnsureTieredStoresCreated() (migrations). Offload with context.Database.ArchiveTierAsync&lt;TRoot&gt;(cutoff) (also synchronous ArchiveTier&lt;TRoot&gt;) and enforce retention with PurgeArchiveOlderThan&lt;TRoot&gt;(olderThan). Idempotent and crash-safe. See docs/TIERED-STORAGE.md and samples/TieredStorage. No changes to existing APIs.

1.0.22
- Build/packaging: ship SourceLink metadata, deterministic (CI) builds, and a .snupkg symbol package so consumers get source-mapped stack traces and step-into debugging; the publish workflow now pushes the symbol package alongside the main package. Enable NuGet package validation against the previous release to guard the public API. Documentation: correct the spatial docs/IntelliSense to state that geometry is stored in DuckDB's native GEOMETRY column type (WKT is only the driver wire format), not WKT-in-VARCHAR. No code or public API changes. (DuckDB.EFCoreProvider.NTS updated to 1.0.6.)

1.0.21
- Update Entity Framework Core dependencies from 10.0.8 to 10.0.9. No code or public API changes.

1.0.20
- Rename the package, assembly, and root namespace from `DuckDB.EFCoreDriver` to `DuckDB.EFCoreProvider`. This is a drop-in rename: update package references to `DuckDB.EFCoreProvider` (and `DuckDB.EFCoreProvider.NTS`) and replace `using DuckDB.EFCoreDriver...` with `using DuckDB.EFCoreProvider...`. No behavioural or public API changes beyond the names.

1.0.19
- Documentation: remove decorative emoji from the README. No code or public API changes.

1.0.18
- The migrations lock now waits a bounded time (default 5 minutes, configurable with `UseDuckDB(o => o.MigrationLockTimeout(...))`, `Timeout.InfiniteTimeSpan` to wait forever) instead of retrying indefinitely. A lock row left behind by a crashed migrator previously hung `database update` / `Migrate()` forever; it now fails with a TimeoutException reporting how long the lock has been held and how to clear it.
- Fix a latent crash in migration-lock contention: when another migrator actually held the lock, the acquisition loop threw a NullReferenceException instead of waiting.

1.0.17
- Polish the shipped IntelliSense documentation: fill previously empty param/returns/exception tags on the public entry points (UseDuckDB, AddDuckDB, EF.Functions row-value comparisons, SQL expression constructors) and fix typos in doc comments and exception messages. No behavioural changes.

1.0.16
- Ship the IntelliSense XML documentation file in the package, so the public API docs appear in consumers' IDEs.
- Add explanatory messages to previously message-less exceptions, most notably the NotSupportedException thrown when generating idempotent migration scripts (a DuckDB engine limitation, as with SQLite).
- Remove three empty placeholder classes (DuckDBTableExtensions, DuckDBTableBuilderExtensions, DuckDBEntityTypeMappingFragmentExtensions) that had no members and no function.
- Documentation: correct docs/MIGRATIONS.md, which wrongly recommended `dotnet ef migrations script --idempotent`; idempotent scripts are not supported. No behavioural changes.

1.0.15
- Documentation: standardise prose on British English spelling. No code or public API changes.

1.0.14
- Documentation: add a runnable Quickstart sample (samples/Quickstart), a Troubleshooting/FAQ section and a configuration &amp; connection-string reference in the README, a migrations guide (docs/MIGRATIONS.md), and a root CHANGELOG. No code or public API changes.

1.0.13
- Add `UseDuckDB(o => o.FileSearchPath("/data"))`: configures DuckDB's `file_search_path` (one or more comma-separated directories that relative file paths — e.g. in `[FromParquet]` — are resolved against) when a connection opens. Documentation refresh.

1.0.12
- Version bump; no functional changes since 1.0.11.

1.0.11
- Internal: load the SQL-generation reserved-word set lazily and resiliently instead of in a static constructor that opens a connection (deferred I/O; graceful degradation instead of a TypeInitializationException). Reduce repeated XML-doc boilerplate and split the query translating visitor and query SQL generator JSON handling into partial classes. No public API or behaviour changes.

1.0.10
- Build hygiene: enforce code style (`EnforceCodeStyleInBuild`) and treat warnings as errors across the repository. No public API or behaviour changes.
- Internal: name the batch script-size estimation constants, note `SharedTypeExtensions` provenance, and DRY the functional-test fixtures onto a shared base.

1.0.9
- Robustness: `Exists()` now determines a file database's existence from the file's presence, so a database whose file exists but is held open by another writer process is no longer misreported as non-existent.
- Scaffolding: emit a warning when a primary/foreign-key column reported as nullable by DuckDB is scaffolded as non-nullable.
- Internal cleanup and additional test coverage (database existence, decimal precision/scale, array round-trips); no public API changes.

1.0.8
- Add `UseDuckDB(o => o.MemoryLimit("4GB"))`: configures DuckDB's `memory_limit` (the buffer-manager cap) when a connection opens. When not set, DuckDB's default of 80% of physical RAM is left unchanged. Accepts DuckDB size syntax (e.g. "4GB", "512MB", "75%").

1.0.7
- Add `context.Upsert(...)` / `UpsertAsync(...)`: high-throughput insert-or-update backed by batched DuckDB `INSERT ... ON CONFLICT (key) DO UPDATE`. Inserts new rows and updates existing ones by primary key in one round-trip per batch (~8x faster than read-then-insert-or-update). Raw fast path (no change tracking / store-generated keys / shadow or computed columns); all mapped non-key columns are overwritten, key-only entities use `ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING`.

1.0.6
- Fix `DateTime.Date` translation to return a `DateTime` (midnight) instead of a `DateOnly`, so projecting or grouping by `.Date` (e.g. chart/panel aggregation) no longer fails with "No coercion operator is defined between types 'System.DateOnly' and 'System.DateTime'".

1.0.5
- Add opt-in `SaveChanges` insert batching (`EnableBulkInsertBatching`): merges consecutive inserts into a single multi-row `INSERT ... VALUES (..),(..)` statement (~10x faster) while keeping change tracking and store-generated keys.
- Add opt-in `SaveChanges` update batching (`EnableBulkUpdateBatching`): merges eligible (primary-key, no computed columns) updates into a single `UPDATE ... FROM (VALUES ..)` statement (~8x faster); updates with concurrency tokens or computed columns fall back to the per-row path.
- Add opt-in `SaveChanges` delete batching (`EnableBulkDeleteBatching`): merges eligible (primary-key) deletes into a single `DELETE ... WHERE key IN (..)` / `DELETE ... USING (VALUES ..)` statement (~14x faster), especially effective for orphan cleanup and child-collection replacement; deletes with concurrency tokens fall back to the per-row path.
- All three are disabled by default and independent; each merged run is atomic. Tune merge size with `MaxBatchSize`.

